node.text:
@USANAinc Active Nutrition is here!!🥳 this Electrolyte Replacement is part of it and essential for the summer heat. .Sponsored 

Dressing
* 3 tbsp olive oil
* 3 tbsp lime juice
* 3 garlic clove, minced
* 2 packets Electrolyte Replacement
For the salad
* 5 cups cubed watermelon 
* 1/4 cup Blueberries
* 1/3 Cup Cucumbers
* 1 medium Avocado, cubed 
* 1/2 Serrano Pepper, sliced
* 2 oz. Feta Cheese, crumbled
* mint to taste
* Sea salt and pepper to taste 
Instructions:
Now let’s get started. First whisk together all dressing ingredients. Set aside. 
Assemble the salad ingredients on a platter as desired. Feel free to add or substitute ingredients as you like! Season to taste and serve with dressing. Perfect for the summer!#LiveUSANA  #USANAactive #salad #summer #watermelon #hydrate

node.title: Watermelon Salad with hydrating watermelon dressing 🥗🍉

node.text:
Sun-Dried Tomato Chicken Burgers with Basil Aioli… super easy, incredibly delicious, and perfect for a grillin 👌by @primal_gourmet 
~
(also works with ground turkey). Serve it on lettuce buns to keep things Whole30 and Paleo, or between your favorite buns. You’re the boss, applesauce!

For the Chicken Burgers:
2 pounds ground chicken substitute ground turkey
1 yellow onion diced
4 cloves garlic finely chopped
2 tablespoons roughly chopped sun-dried tomatoes packed in olive oil
1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh oregano substitute 1 teaspoon dried oregano
1 teaspoon dried basil
2 teaspoons kosher salt – plus extra for sautéed onions
1 teaspoon freshly-cracked black pepper
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil
1 teaspoon avocado oil
1 head iceberg lettuce cut into bun shapes
sliced red onions for serving

node.text:
Paleo Lemon Butter Chicken
This is easy to make, is full of fresh flavors, and is so delicious! By @realfoodwithjessica 

Ingredients
8 chicken thighs, bone-in skin-on
1 lemon, zested and juiced
3 tablespoons ghee**
1/4 cup coconut cream
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder*
1/2 teaspoon salt
2 tablespoons chopped fresh rosemary
Instructions
Preheat the oven to 375° and place the chicken thighs skin side down in a 13x9 pan.
Sprinkle lightly with salt then flip over so the skin side is up. Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine lemon zest and juice, ghee, coconut cream, garlic powder, salt, and rosemary.
Stir over medium heat until everything is well combined.
Pour the mixture over the thighs and bake for 40-45 minutes or until they reach 165°.
If you want the skin crispy, turn up the oven to 500° and bake for another 5-10 minutes.

STRAWBERRY FIELDS GRILLED CHICKEN WRAP🍓🍓🍓 great for using up the last of the summer strawberries 
By • @alltypesofbowls

this wrap is loaded with greens, fresh strawberries, walnuts, grilled chicken, goat cheese, and a sweet balsamic dressing. 

STRAWBERRY FIELDS GRILLED CHICKEN WRAP
ingredients:
grilled chicken breast 
spinach
arugula
sliced strawberries
cherry tomatoes
sliced mini peppers
chopped walnuts
crumbled goat cheese
2 tbsp balsamic
2 tbsp olive oil
honey
pinch of salt
pinch of pepper

directions:
add the spinach and arugula to the wrap first. 
then add in the chicken, strawberries, tomatoes, peppers, walnuts and goat cheese. 
make your dressing by whisking the balsamic, olive oil, honey, salt and pepper together and drizzle that over top.
wrap it up, cut in half and enjoy!

Happy Friday! Tis the season~
Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Stovetop Oatmeal 🎃
by @thechowdown

It’s finally that time of year for hot oatmeal again. Gimme all the stovetop oats, baked oats and blended oats! Save this for when you need a cozy & festive breakfast.

Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Oatmeal
1/2 cup rolled oats
1 cup milk of choice
1/4 cup pumpkin purée
1-2 tbsp maple syrup (depending on how sweet you like your oatmeal)
1/2 tsp cinnamon
1/2 tsp pumpkin pie spice
Pinch of salt
1. Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, approximately 8-10 minutes.
2. Pour oatmeal into a bowl and top with chocolate chips (and maple syrup, optional)

What bowl 🥣 is your go to!?? 1️⃣↔️6️⃣ comment below and let me know!👇 
All these by @daliciousdish 
-
1️⃣BURGER BOWL🍔 
.
.
Loaded burger bowls! A bowl of all the goods!
.
.
80/20 ground Chuck 
Colbey Jack cheese 
Bread & butter pickles 
sweet potato fries 
Avocado 
Grape tomatoes 
Red onions 
.
. 
#dEATS Burger patties seasoned with sea salt and pepper. Air-fry the sweet potato fries at 400 degrees for 15 mins.Hope everyone is having a wonderful day!

2️⃣ Shrimp bowl 🦐 
.
.
A bowl of all the goods! I had some lettuce I needed to use and decided to make a loaded salad bowl!
.
.
Pan seared jumbo shrimp
Black beans 
Grape tomatoes
Corn
double roasted salsa for dressing
.
. 
#dEATS Shrimp seasoned with garlic powder, smoked paprika, sea salt and pepper. On medium heat, sear each side for 2-3 mins with avocado oil. 
.
3️⃣turmeric falafel 
Campari tomatoes
Cucumbers
Feta cheese
Kalamata olives 
.
.
4️⃣Chicken Cobb🥗 
.
.
Nothing like a classic salad for dinner tonight! 
.
.
Grilled chicken breast 
Spring mix
Grape tomatoes
Avocado 
Red onions 
Blue cheese crumbles 
boiled eggs
.
.
#dEATS Grilled chicken breast seasoned with garlic powder, smoked paprika, S&P. You can bake at 375 for 42-45 mins. For dressing, I used regular balsamic vinegar!

5️⃣Blue Cheese Steak
.
.
We all know that avocado & toast pairs perfect, but man does steak & blue cheese pairs perfectly, too 😍
.
.
6oz filet
Spring mix
Campari tomatoes
Red onions
Avocado
Blue cheese 
Balsamic vinegar for dressing 
.
.
#dEATS Grilled 6oz filet seasoned with lemon pepper, sea salt, & fresh cracked pepper! 

6️⃣SALSA VERDE CHICKEN BOWL 
.
.
It’s definitely an easy crockpot meal day! 
.
.
3 chicken breasts
2  Salsa Verde jars
Lettuce
Brown rice
Black beans
Grape tomatoes
Limes
.
.
#dEATS I put 3 chicken breast in my crockpot seasoned with sea salt and pepper. Then poured 2 salsa verde jars on top and cook at low heat for 6-7 hours. Shredded with two forks and it’s ready to go!

Game changer for weekday dinners 👉🏼 have your veggies/bases prepped ahead of time!🙌
Flank steak with sweet potato wedges & roasted broccolini ⏩
By @kissmywheatgrass_
INGREDIENTS
Flank steak
ghee
Sweet potato
Baby broccolini 
Seasonings- paprika, oregano, onion, garlic, salt, pepper
Olive oil
.
.
DIRECTIONS
Cut up the sweet potato & coat with olive oil & seasoning. Place on parchment paper on a baking sheet & cook in the oven for 45 mins at 375. Flip halfway through. *These come out slightly crispy on the outside and softer on the inside. .
Heat oil on the stove and place steak (coat it in the seasonings first) in the pan with the top on. Cook to your liking then top with ghee or butter.
.
Drizzle broccolini with olive oil & sprinkle garlic powder on the broccolini then bake at 375 for 12 min.

Tip for veggie prep: so you can build your meal in real time throughout the week. This doesn’t *always happen* but I shoot to roast/steam various veggies, bake some sweet potato fries, cut/wash greens, etc on Sundays. Then each night throughout the week all I have to do is make the protein & add my prepped ingredients! Sometimes I prep the chicken, steak, etc ahead of time too but I think this tastes better fresh 😛 
.

node.text:
Cookie Dough Ice Cream Sandwiches 🍦Vegan, paleo, and gluten free 👌🏼 What an epic combo by @choosing_balance

My summer obsession has always been banana ice cream but by the end of summer we have to switch things up a bit 😉 -
-
-
-
Ingredients: 
Cookie dough: 
1 cup almond flour 
1/4 cup coconut sugar 
1/4 cup softened coconut oil (not melted completely) 
2 tsp vanilla 
1/4 cup almond milk
1/2 tsp salt 
Ice Cream: 
3 frozen bananas 
3 tbsp cashew butter 
2 tsp vanilla 
Sprinkle of salt -

Instructions: 
For the cookie dough: Mix all of the ingredients together well besides the chocolate chips. Then fold in the chocolate chips. Line a 8x8 or 9x5 brownie pan with parchment paper (if you double this recipe, use a small cookie sheet instead) 
Press the cookie dough into the pan and flatten it out. 
Place in the freezer for two hours 
When the cookie dough is almost done, make the ice cream 
Blend all of the ice cream ingredients together.
Then remove the cookie dough and cut into 6 rectangles (can do squares too) 
Then add ice cream to one half and press the other half on top of each piece, making the sandwiches.
Place back in the freezer for another hour or until the ice cream is hardened. 
Remove and enjoy immediately! Store in the freezer. Makes 3 big ice cream sandwiches. #plantbaseddiet #icecream #veganrecipes #healthyrecipes
